1 Preheat the oven to 400°F. 2 Combine the pears with the zest, sugar, nutmeg, and ½ cup water in the bottom of a large baking dish. 3 Mix the dry ingredients together, then rub in the butter. 4 Sprinkle this mixture on top of the pears and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until the top is golden. Serve warm with low-sugar custard.